    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "History": {
          "text": "Acute unilateral\nvision loss\n, decreased color sensation, and/or\nvisual field deficit\nafter blunt or penetrating trauma\nComplaints may be delayed due to the impact of and treatment for other concomitant head injuries",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Physical_Exam": {
          "text": "External eye exam may show signs of\norbital trauma\nor\nfracture\n(soft tissue edema, hematoma, step-off on palpation of orbital rim)\nDecreased visual acuity\nand an afferent pupillary defect (in unilateral cases)\nOn\nfundoscopy\n, the initial optic nerve head assessment will be normal; optic atrophy may be seen 3-6 weeks after trauma",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
